      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 668: The new RR path no longer preserves the previous restart grace period. The old code ignored RTCP loss for DELAY_AFTER_RESTART + 1s, but this only waits 2s after lastMediaRestart_. Because DELAY_AFTER_RESTART is 1s, this may now feed stale pre-restart loss into the controller one second earlier and trigger an immediate decrease after a bitrate/encoder restart. Keep the same effective delay or make the stale window explicit and equivalent.\n```suggestion\nstatic constexpr auto STALE_REPORT_DELAY \u003d DELAY_AFTER_RESTART + std::chrono::seconds(1);\nif (clock::now() - lastMediaRestart_ \u003e\u003d STALE_REPORT_DELAY) {\n```\n",
