      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 675: On Android, the preprocessor guard leaves an unconditional block, so every valid RTCP report is fed to the controller regardless of jitter. On non-Android, the block is gated by rtcpi.jitter \u003c\u003d 1000. This is hard to read and easy to break because the braces are controlled by the #if. Prefer an explicit boolean guard so both paths are clear and maintainable.\n```suggestion\n#if !__ANDROID__\n            const bool validJitter \u003d rtcpi.jitter \u003c\u003d 1000;\n#else\n            const bool validJitter \u003d true;\n#endif\n            if (validJitter) {\n                auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.update(rtcpi.packetLoss,\n                                                       static_cast\u003cfloat\u003e(rtcpi.jitter),\n                                                       rtcpi.latency);\n                setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n            }\n```\n",
      "revId": "d23d187b259eec3261fb5609cd89b6b1a8982e25",
