      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 705: videoBitrateInfo_ and the controller are updated before sender_-\u003esetBitrate() is known to have succeeded. If setBitrate() returns -1, or restartSender() fails after ret \u003d\u003d 0, the stored/current bitrate and controller target diverge from the encoder\u0027s real bitrate. That can make future AIMD decisions operate on a bitrate that was never applied. Move state persistence and bwController_.syncAppliedBitrate(newBR) after a successful encoder update, or roll back on failure.\n```suggestion\nif (sender_) {\n    auto ret \u003d sender_-\u003esetBitrate(newBR);\n    if (ret \u003d\u003d -1) {\n        JAMI_ERROR(\"Fail to access the encoder\");\n        return;\n    }\n    if (ret \u003d\u003d 0) {\n        restartSender();\n        lastMediaRestart_ \u003d clock::now();\n    }\n\n    videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent \u003d newBR;\n    storeVideoBitrateInfo();\n    bwController_.syncAppliedBitrate(newBR);\n} else {\n    JAMI_ERROR(\"Fail to access the sender\");\n}\n```\n",
